        <div xml:id="AN22-kilavi"></div>
        <div xml:id="AN22">
            <lg type="edition"><l>aṇaṅkuṭai neṭuvarai yucciyi ṉiḻitaruṅ</l>
<l>kaṇaṅko ḷaruvik kāṉkeḻu nāṭaṉ</l>
<l>maṇaṅkamaḻ viyaṉmār paṇaṅkiya cella</l>
<l>lituveṉa vaṟiyā maṟuvaraṟ poḻutiṟ</l>
<l>paṭiyōrt tēytta palpukaḻt taṭakkai</l>
<l>neṭuvēṭ pē<supplied>ṇa</supplied>t taṇikuva ḷivaḷeṉa</l>
<l>mutuvāyp peṇṭi <choice><seg>ratuvāy</seg><seg>ratuvāyk</seg></choice> <choice><seg>kūṟak</seg><seg>kūṟa</seg></choice></l>
<l>kaḷanaṉ kiḻaittuk kaṇṇi cūṭṭi</l>
<l><choice><seg>vaḷanakar</seg><seg>vaḷanakarc</seg></choice> cilampap pāṭip palikoṭut</l>
<l>turuvac centiṉai kurutiyoṭu tūuy</l>
<l>murukāṟṟup paṭutta vurukeḻu neṭunā</l>
<l>ḷāra nāṟa varuviṭart tatainta</l>
<l>cāraṟ palpū vaṇṭupaṭac cūṭik</l>
<l>kaḷiṟṟirai ta<supplied>rī</supplied>iya pārva lotukki</l>
<l>ṉoḷittiyaṅku marapiṉ vayappuli pōla</l>
<l>naṉmaṉai neṭunakark kāvala <choice><seg>raṟiyāmai</seg><seg>raṟiyāmait</seg></choice></l>
<l>taṉṉacai yuḷḷattu naṉṉacai vāyppa</l>
<l>viṉṉuyir <choice><seg>kuḻaiya</seg><seg>kuḻaippa</seg></choice> muyaṅkutoṟu meymmalintu</l>
<l>nakkaṉe ṉallaṉō yāṉē yeytta</l>
<l>nōytaṇi kātalar varavīṇ</l>
<l>ṭētil vēlaṟ kulantamai kaṇṭē.</l></lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>At the time of confusion when it was not known that this</l>
<l>was the distress that tormented [her]: the wide chest scented with fragrance</l>
<l>of the man from the forested land with waterfalls in groups,</l>
<l>that tumble down from the peaks of haunted long mountains,</l>
<l>when old truth[-saying] women told that as truth:</l>
<l>“she will be appeased when respect is paid to tall Vēḷ</l>
<l>with much famed broad hands who reduced [his] enemies”,</l>
<l>on the dreadful long day that sets Murukaṉ on [his] way,</l>
<l>well preparing the floor, putting on chaplets,</l>
<l>singing so that the flourishing mansion resounds, giving offerings,</l>
<l>scattering shapely red millet along with blood,</l>
<l>I,</l>
<l>[my] body gladdened in every embrace, for [my] sweet life to turn soft,</l>
<l>when he reached with good yearning in his yearning mind,</l>
<l>without the watchmen of the long mansion, the good house knowing,</l>
<l rend="indent">	like a strong tiger, with the habit of moving stealthily</l>
<l rend="indent">	to a spot for peering out for the elephant bull in order to bring prey,</l>
<l>wearing, for bees to come, many flowers from the slope</l>
<l>that was dense with difficult clefts, while fragrant with sandal,</l>
<l rend="indent5">	    did I not smile,</l>
<l>– seeing the devastation of the strange spear-bearing [priest]</l>
<l>at [our] lover’s coming here in order to appease [our] weary pain?</l></lg>
        </div>
    </body>
